'''Kashiko-dokoro''' (賢所, also read as Kensho{{Sfn|皇典講究所|1908|p=2}})  
The '''Kashiko-dokoro''' is the location within the '''Imperial Palace''' (宮中) of Japan where the '''{{ill|Yata no Kagami|ja|八咫鏡|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}''', one of the [[Three Sacred Treasures of Japan|'''Three Sacred Treasures''']] (三種の神器) and the sacred mirror of the goddess '''[[Amaterasu]]''', is enshrined. Currently, it is one of the '''Kyūchū Sanden''' (宮中三殿) in the '''Imperial Palace'''{{Sfn|中澤伸弘|2010|p=45}}. Before the modern era, it was also called '''Naishidokoro''' (内侍所){{Sfn|中澤伸弘|2010|p=46}}.

'''Kashiko-dokoro''' (かしこどころ、けんしょ{{Sfnp|皇典講究所|1908|p=2}}) is a place in the [[Japan|Japanese]] [[Emperor]]'s [[imperial court]] where the sacred mirror ({{ill|Yata no Kagami|ja|八咫鏡|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}), one of the [[Three Sacred Treasures of Japan]] and the spirit of [[Amaterasu Omikami]], is enshrined. In the current [[Imperial Palace]] it is one of the {{ill|Three Palace Sanctuaries|ja|宮中三殿|1=Three Palace Sanctuaries|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} {{Sfnp|中澤伸弘|2010|p=45}}.

