== Overview ==  

The {{ill|Three Palace Sanctuaries|ja|宮中三殿|1=Three Palace Sanctuaries|qq=draft|qq=draft}} '''(Kyūchū Sanden)''' face south and consist of the '''Kashiko-dokoro''' at the center, the '''Kōreiden''' to the west, and the '''Shinden''' to the east{{Sfn|中澤伸弘|2010|p=45}}. Among these three sanctuaries, the '''Kashiko-dokoro''' is regarded as the most sacred, and its floor is raised approximately one shaku (about 30 centimeters) higher than the others{{Sfn|中澤伸弘|2010|p=46}}. The structure is divided into three sections:  
* '''Outer Chamber''' (外陣): Accessible only to members of the Imperial family.
* '''Inner Chamber''' (内陣): Accessible only to the Emperor and Empress.
* '''Innermost Chamber''' (内々陣): The space where the sacred mirror and '''Amaterasu''' are enshrined.

The '''Inner Chamber''' of the '''Kashiko-dokoro''' features two '''eternal lamps''' (常夜灯){{Sfn|皇室編集部|2017|pp=42-43}}.  

Historically, the '''Kashiko-dokoro''' was also known as '''Naishidokoro''', referencing the sacred mirror's earlier placement in the '''Onmeiden''' before its relocation to a separate hall{{Efn2|The transition of the sacred mirror from the Emperor’s chamber to the Onmeiden, and later its designation as Naishidokoro, is detailed in several sources, such as the {{ill|Sarashina Nikki|ja|更級日記|qq=draft|qq=draft}} and {{ill|The Tale of Genji|ja|源氏物語|qq=draft|qq=draft}}'s "Makibashira" chapter{{Sfn|橋本富太郎|2005|p=59}}{{Sfn|中澤伸弘|2010|p=46}}.}}. Various kanji have been used for "Kashiko-dokoro," including '''恐所''', '''畏所''', '''威所''', '''尊所''', and '''貴所'''{{Sfn|皇典講究所|1908|pp=1-2}}.  

Daily offerings ('''Nikkū''') are conducted in the '''Kashiko-dokoro''' by the '''Naishoten''', and Imperial rituals ('''Myōchō Goyōhai''') are performed daily without interruption{{Sfn|松山能夫|1966|pp=121-123}}. Additionally, special ceremonies such as the '''Seasonal Festivals''' (旬祭), the '''Kashiko-dokoro Ritual of Kanname-sai''' in October, and the '''Kashiko-dokoro Mikagura Ritual''' in December are held annually{{Sfn|中澤伸弘|2010|pp=64-92}}.  

